The UK is working with the Kenyan government and airlines to increase the number of flights to the UK before the flight suspension at 23:59 (local time) on Wednesday 25 March. Sign up for email alerts for the latest advice.
Kenya Airways are laying on an extra flight to Amsterdam for EU and British nationals at 2200 on 25 March. Contact Kenya Airways on +254 741 131 526 or contactcenterbackoffice@kenya-airways.com for bookings. There remain a number of options for flights from Amsterdam to several UK destinations; these will need to be booked separately.
Contact your tour operator or airline for the latest information on any possible disruptions, cancellations or reduction of flight services, in advance of the suspension of international flights.
Foreigners, including British nationals, can break self-quarantine arrangements only if asymptomatic and only to depart Kenya immediately, before international flights are suspended.
We are working with the Kenyan government and airlines to increase the number of flights to the UK before the flight suspension. British Nationals in need of urgent help, please contact the British High Commission via http://www.gov.uk/contact-consulate-nairobi
If you are vulnerable with health issues, an older person, or will be travelling with young children, you can call: +254202844000 or +254 20 287 3000 and follow the options for consular assistance. The numbers are available 24/7.
